  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6558.53 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-14.99B) and positive gamma peak at 6580 (+4.02B), dealers are in active hedging mode - buying into any dips toward 6550 and selling rallies toward 6580, creating amplified two-way volatility in this tight 30-point range. The breakout regime with -75.9B total GEX means dealers will continue this destabilizing flow, and the recent wall_break/gex_surge events suggest we just saw violent hedging activity that's likely to persist. Watch 6550 as the critical support where dealer buying should intensify, while 6580 becomes the key resistance where dealer selling pressure kicks in.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect whippy, trending moves with dealers amplifying both bounces off 6550 and rejections at 6580.",
